This is the README file for Package::Constants, a module that lets you
list all constants defined in a package.

Please refer to 'perldoc Package::Constants' after installation for 
details.

#####################################################################

* Description

Package::Constants

    Package::Constants lists all the constants defined in a certain 
    package. This can be useful for, among others, setting up an 
    autogenerated @EXPORT/@EXPORT_OK for a Constants.pm file.

#####################################################################

* Installation

Package::Constants follows the standard perl module install process

perl Makefile.PL
make
make test
make install

The module uses no C or XS parts, so no c-compiler is required.

